climbs.name: My Feets, My Feets, My Precious Feeet
climbs.fa: FA: Pete Delannoy, Howard Doyle, and Verne Phinney, July 5, 1985.

content.description:
Starts at the bottom of the gully on north west corner. Step off the fin / flake and crystal climb upward and left through 3 new bolts. From the third bolt head for the horizontal crack that takes small gear. Move strait up from the horizontal to a pod with a finger crack. From here you can see a bolt up and a ways out left. continue left on good holds past some more bolts to summit.  

  Anchor in a slung horn backed up by a lone button head 

  1 70 m will get you safely down the face or swing right into gully with a 60 m
content.location: right corner of the North side of west lies mirkwood

climbs.name: Knob Goblin
climbs.fa: Lee Terveen, Joel McKillop, Chris Hirsch (Ground-Up)

content.description: Stunning center line leaving you wanting more. Great incuts the whole way, yet thought provoking to reach each bolt. Bullet rock and a nice belay on top.
content.protection: 8 Bolts   Medium gear for horizontal (red & yellow c3(maybe some tri-cams would be better?))   Bolted chain anchors
content.location: Begin in middle of N Face. Single 70m rap.

content.description: This formation is part of the Near Downs rib but a separate summit immediately to the NE. First ascent of this spire is unknown...??
